                StorySection(title = "He Does Everything Well", text = "Jesus commanded them not to tell anyone. But the more He did so, the more they kept talking about it. People were overwhelmed with amazement. 'He has done everything well,' they said. 'He even makes the deaf hear and the mute speak.' This is an echo of the 'Good' of Creation in Genesis. Jesus was 're-creating' what had been broken. He was restoring the 'Very Good' to the human experience.\n\nThe Decapolis—a Gentile region—was seeing the power of the Jewish Messiah. Jesus was showing that His 'Ephphatha' was for everyone. He does everything 'well' because He is the Master Architect. He doesn't just 'patch' our lives; He Loosens the chains that bind us. He is the God of the complete restoration. The man wasn't just 'mumbling' anymore; he was 'speaking plainly.' Excellence is the signature of Christ."),
                StorySection(title = "Be Opened", text = "What 'Ephphatha' do you need in your life today? Are you 'deaf' to the voice of God because of the 'crowds' of noise around you? Do you 'hardly talk' about the things that matter because your heart is bound by fear or shame? Jesus is inviting you to get 'away from the crowd.'\n\nLet Him touch your 'ears' and your 'tongue.' Invite Him into the messiness of your inability. Hear the 'deep sigh' of His love for you. Don't be afraid to be 'opened.' He wants you to hear His promises and to speak His praise. He does everything well—including the restoration of your soul. Ephphatha! Be opened to the Grace of the King.")
